<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-10-25T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-10-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="54" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4 A 2/121b: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-25T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 25,
                                        1924—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>84. American Delegation to Opium Conference at Geneva will consist of
                            Honorable Stephen G. Porter, chairman, Eight Reverend Charles H. Brent,
                            Assistant Surgeon General Rupert Blue, Mrs. Hamilton Wright, Mr. Edwin
                            L. Neville, delegates, with five assistants and clerks. Please notify
                            Secretary General of League of Nations and the appropriate Swiss
                            authorities.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
